  "text": "The HTTP filter chain extension mechanism in envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2 is composed of several key architectural components:\n\n## Filter Factory Registry\nThe filter factory registry is defined through the `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` interface (envoy/server/filter_config.h) which all HTTP filter factories must implement. The concrete registry managers are implemented in source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h: `HttpFilterConfigProviderManagerImpl` manages downstream HTTP filter configurations and `UpstreamHttpFilterConfigProviderManagerImpl` manages upstream HTTP filter configurations.\n\n## Filter Context\nThe filter context is represented by the `FilterContext` struct (envoy/http/filter_factory.h) which contains the filter configuration name and filter extension name. Additionally, `Server::Configuration::FactoryContext` and `Server::Configuration::UpstreamFactoryContext` provide the broader context for filter creation.\n\n## Per-Request Filter Chain Execution\nThe per-request filter chain execution is orchestrated by:\n1. `FilterManager` (source/common/http/filter_manager.h/cc) - Manages the per-request filter chain state and iteration through filters\n2. `ConnectionManagerImpl` (source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h/cc) - Creates new filter chains for each HTTP stream\n3. `FilterChainFactory` interface and its implementation `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h/cc) - Constructs the filter chains based on configuration\n\n## Key Extension Points\nThe extension mechanism defines:\n- `FilterFactoryCb` (envoy/http/filter_factory.h) - A function callback that instantiates filters\n- `FilterChainManager` (envoy/http/filter_factory.h) - Interface for building filter chains at runtime\n- `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` (envoy/http/filter.h) - Callbacks used by filter factories to add filters to a chain\n- `StreamDecoderFilter`, `StreamEncoderFilter`, and `StreamFilter` (envoy/http/filter.h) - The actual filter interfaces that implementations extend\n\n## Configuration and Discovery\nDynamic filter configuration is handled through:\n- `FilterConfigProvider` template (envoy/filter/config_provider_manager.h) for managing static and dynamic filter configs\n- `HttpDynamicFilterConfigProviderImpl` (source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h) for runtime HTTP filter discovery\n- `FilterChainHelper` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h/cc) for processing filter configurations and dependencies\n\nThe chain execution flow: HTTP connection arrives → ConnectionManagerImpl → HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain → FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb → FilterManager performs per-request iteration through decoder/encoder filters (decodeHeaders, decodeData, encodeHeaders, encodeData, etc.)"
}

